r limits imply a\ndisk-averaged water abundance of $\\lesssim 10^{-6}$ with respect to H$_2$ for\nClass I objects. After taking into account the physical structure of the disk,\nthe upper limit to the water abundance averaged over the inner warm disk with\n$T>$ 100 K is between 10$^{-7}$ up to 10$^{-5}$. Water vapor is not abundant in\nwarm protostellar envelopes around Class I protostars. Upper limits to the\nwater vapor column densities in Class I disks are at least two orders magnitude\nlower than values found in Class 0 disk-like structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Feb 2020 03:21:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-15"}
