e with those obtained from non-cluster abundance cosmological probes\nsuch as Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB), Baryonic Acoustic Oscillation (BAO),\nand supernovae (SNe). The joint analysis of our cluster data with\nPlanck18+BAO+Pantheon gives \\om ~$=0.315^{+0.013}_{-0.011}$ and \\sig\n~$=0.810^{+0.011}_{-0.010}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Feb 2020 04:11:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Jul 2020 21:55:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 1 Aug 2020 11:05:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-07"}
